urons and over 54.5 million synapses. It took the team over four years to c=
onstruct the brain map and during the process, they discovered over 8,000 p=
reviously undiscovered types of neurons.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The map is an=
 unprecedented, detailed resource for how the brain functions. Sure, it&#82=
17;s a fruit fly brain, but this is how this process usually works: the fru=
it fly is simple, so we map it early, learn a bunch, and then apply those l=
earnings to larger animals, then humans. Scientists have started with fruit=
 flies to study genetics and inheritance, gene mapping and linkage, circadi=
an rhythms, and more. Which is to say, understanding these guys&#8217; litt=
le brains could provide new insights on how our big brains work. </p><p sty=
